{{version030}}
{{flavour|Weaves illusions of the caster. Such illusions have the same physical prowess as the original, and can cast the same spells.}}

'''Mara Summon''' is a monsters-only spell which temporarily creates up to two near-identical clones of the [[unique]] [[rakshasa]] [[Mara]]. These clones have all of Mara's stats, including his current health, and can cast any of his spells except for Mara Summon and [[Summon Illusion]]. The real Mara may immediately swap positions with one of the two clones upon creating them; this makes it impossible to tell which Mara is the real one. The clones will disappear after enough time has passed, and are vulnerable to abjuration (via [[Yara's Violent Unravelling]]).

{{monsters with spell}}

==History==
*Prior to [[0.15]], Mara could not swap places with his clones upon summoning them.

